freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: I have the worst post-menstrual-period vaginal yeast infection Ive ever experienced. By day 6 or 7 of my period, my vagina, vulva, and groin were dark red, burning/itching, and I may have had fever. I felt fatigued and sleep was disturbed.

My swollen lymph nodes got better, then swelled up and got sore again the last couple of days. It was mild soreness and swelling, noticeable but not disruptive. They are starting to decrease in size and soreness, with rest.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Cough, chest congestion, post nasal drip and shortness of breath
Swollen underarm lymph nodes, breast pain, ovarian pain
